-------------------------
Logistical Mission Strategy Generator - In collaboration with Fleets-Online B.V. (https://fleets-online.com/)
-------------------------
Description
This Knowledge-Based Engineering application can be used to generate the best strategy for logistical problems
in for example the agricultural, construction and transportation industries. The application uses fleet data
provided by the user and iterates over possible strategies to come up with a winning strategy, based on a weighted function
concerning one or more of the following goals: Time, Cost and/or Emissions (CO2 + NOx),
including the possibility of strict deadlines.
-------------------------
Usage
To run the application, one should first specify its fleet, depot, and work site location in a JSON format.
After that, the user should run the file 'main.py'. this file will instantiate the root object, called
'MissionStrategyApp'. A ParaPy GUI will open, and the user can already look at a fleet visualisation on a map by pressing on 'root'
on the upper left corner of the screen. The user should specify its mission preferences, needed machinery,
amount of total man-hours corresponding to that needed machinery. In case there are strict deadlines (by pressing the check-box),
the user should include the start time and deadline time. After that, to that which contains buttons to run the mission generator,
visualize different outputs and alter the used data.
-------------------------
Dependencies
---
APIs
The FleetsOnline API is used by sending requests to 'https://api.v2.deepdigital.org', which requires a FleetsOnline
account for authentication.
The OpenRouteService API is used, which requires an ORS account for authentication.
---
Libraries
parapy v1.15.1
kbeutils v1.0
routingpy v1.3.1
numpy v2.4.6
requests v2.34.2
reportlab v4.5.1
